===Etymology===
Latin ''[[igneus]]'', from ''[[ignis]]'' fire; allied to Sanskrit ''[[agni]]'', Lithuanian ''[[ugnis]]'', Old Slavic ''[[ogne]]''
===Igneous===
#Pertaining to, having the nature of, fire; containing fire; resembling fire; as, an '''igneous''' appearance
#''(Geology):'' Resulting from, or produced by, the action of fire; as, lavas and basalt are '''igneous''' rocks